==English==

===Etymology===
Greek [[εκφρασις]], from [[εκφραζειν]], from [[εκ-]] ‘ex-’ + [[φραζειν]] ‘speak’.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/'ɛkfrəsɪs/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|ecphras|es}}

# (''Rhetoric'') A clear, intense, self-contained [[argument]] or pictorial [[description]] of an object, especially of an artwork.

